summary: The Las Vegas Raiders have had a busy week as they prepare for the upcoming season. On Monday, the team announced that Gardner Minshew has been named starting quarterback, beating out Aidan O'Connell for the position. Head coach Antonio Pierce made the announcement after the Raiders lost 27-12 to the Dallas Cowboys in their second preseason game. The Raiders' loss to the Cowboys was their second in a row, following a 24-19 defeat to the Jacksonville Jaguars in their first preseason game. The Raiders will have one more preseason game before the regular season begins, when they face the New England Patriots on Friday, August 25.

name: Daniel Jones
summary: Daniel Jones' preseason return with the Giants was marred by two interceptions, including a pick-six. Head coach Brian Daboll acknowledged Jones' poor decision-making but expressed relief that the errors occurred in a preseason game. Despite the miscues, the Giants' second preseason game showcased other storylines, including the team's progress in the absence of Saquon Barkley. Meanwhile, Tom Brady drew attention for seemingly criticizing Jones during a discussion about his broadcasting approach. Former Pro Bowl receiver Brandon Marshall went as far as calling Jones' performance "unethical." However, Jones' performance should be viewed in the context of a preseason game where the primary objective is to prepare for the regular season.
